The '''Institut Néerlandais''' (1957–2013) was a non-profit institution in [[Paris]] devoted to the promotion of [[Culture of the Netherlands|Dutch art and culture]]. One of the earliest foreign [[cultural center]]s in Paris, it was founded in 1957 by [[Frits Lugt]]. The [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Netherlands)|Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs]], the sole financier of the center announced its closure in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2676/Cultuur/article/detail/3390761/2013/02/08/Institut-Neerlandais-gaat-eind-dit-jaar-dicht.dhtml|title=Institut Néerlandais gaat eind dit jaar dicht|date=8 February 2013|work=[[de Volkskrant]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=9 February 2013}}</ref> It closed in December 2013.
