{{Infobox library | library_name = National Archives and Library of Ethiopia | name_en = | library_logo = | image = File:Logo-National Archives and Library of Ethiopia.jpg | caption = | country = | type = national library | scope = | established = 1944 | ref_legal_mandate = proclamation No. 179/1999 | location = [[Addis Ababa]] | coordinates = | branch_of = | num_branches = | items_collected = books, [[periodical literature]], [[microform]], [[photographs]], [[manuscript]], [[Academic paper|research paper]] | collection_size = | criteria = | legal_deposit = yes | req_to_access = | annual_circulation = | pop_served = researchers, government and nongovernment organizations, employees, students {{refn|group=nb|According to the United Nations, as of 2007 approximately 38 percent of adult Ethiopians are [[Literacy#Literacy in Africa|literate]].<ref name=UnescoLiteracy>{{cite web|url= http://data.uis.unesco.org/Index.aspx?DataSetCode=EDULIT_DS&popupcustomise=true&lang=en# |title= Adult literacy rate, population 15+ years (both sexes, female, male) |publisher= [[UNESCO Institute for Statistics]] |location=Montreal |work=UIS.Stat |accessdate=25 August 2017 }}</ref>}} | members = | budget = | director = Mr. Ato Abreham Chosha | num_employees = | website = http://www.nale.gov.et/national_library.html | phone_num = | references = }}
The '''National Archives and Library of [[Ethiopia]]''', located in [[Addis Ababa]], is the [[national library]] and [[national archives|archives]] of the country. The library was inaugurated in 1944 by Emperor [[Haile Selassie]] and began service with books donated by the emperor.<ref name="About Us: Home Page" />
==Overview== In 1976, proclamation No. 50/76 gave the library the legal right to collect three copies of every material published in the country.{{Citation needed|reason=reliable source needed for the whole sentence|date=September 2013}} In 1999, the library was reestablished by proclamation no. 179.1999 as a national institution, which resulted in structural changes and the mission to be one of the top five national libraries and archives in Africa by 2020.<ref name="About Us: Home Page">{{cite web|title=About Us|url=http://www.nala.gov.et/Pages/CommonPage.aspx?Id=1|work=Ethiopian National Archives and Library Agency|accessdate=28 September 2013}}</ref> It is currently a unit of the [[Ministry of Culture and Tourism (Ethiopia)|Ministry of Culture and Tourism]].
The archives was established in 1979, and its collection includes ancient and historical [[manuscript]]s written from as early as the 14th and 15th centuries. It started functioning with archives from the Ministry of the Grand Palace, Palace of the Crown Prince, and others. The archive includes letters written by several kings, empresses, and princes.
