An '''outfit of the day''' (commonly abbreviated '''OOTD'''<ref>{{cite book|title=The Internet: The Book Of Revelations, Volume 5|date=2012|publisher=Books on Demand|isbn=3848254530|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=q-YfSiucT_EC&pg=PT197&dq=outfit+of+the+day+ootd&hl=en&sa=X&ei=13N2U820JaHlsASltYGIAw&ved=0CDIQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=outfit%20of%20the%20day%20ootd&f=false|author=Felix von Keudell|accessdate=May 16, 2014}}</ref>) is where [[fashion blog]]gers show what [[clothes]] (or outfits) they wear on a particular day or occasion. These are often found on social media websites, such as [[Tumblr]], [[Instagram]], and [[Pinterest]], as well as various videos on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Leah Gonzalez |url=http://www.psfk.com/2014/03/zappos-instagram-clothing-recommendations.html#!N9cKa |title=Zappos Creates Personalized Shopping Experience For Instagram's #OOTD Fans |publisher=PSFK |date=March 21, 2014 |accessdate=May 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tumblr.com/tagged/outfit-of-the-day |title=outfit of the day on Tumblr |publisher=Tumblr.com |date= |accessdate=May 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinterest.com/vuhhnessasays/fashion-style-ootd/ |title=Fashion/Style/OOTD on Pinterest |publisher=Pinterest.com |date= |accessdate=May 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/search?num=100&safe=off&site=&source=hp&q=youtube+outfits+of+the+day&oq=youtube+outfits+of+the+day&gs_l=hp.3..0i22i30.378.7384.0.7694.31.27.2.2.3.4.399.3989.11j7j8j1.27.0....0...1c.1.43.hp..9.22.1934.0.9blYOk40MbU|title=youtube outfits of the day - Google Search|website=www.google.com}}</ref> Mostly used by a younger female demographic, one example of a typical current outfit of the day would be a top from [[Forever 21]], low rise jeans from [[American Eagle Outfitters|American Eagle]], [[UGG Australia]] boots, as well as some accessories including a [[Coach Inc.|Coach]] [[Handbag|purse]], [[makeup]], and various [[jewelry]]. Similar to these blogs are known as "outfit(s) of the week" (OOTW), where the blogger will display what they plan to wear during a whole week (or several days).
